<graph edgedefault="undirected"><node id="BANK OF WISCONSIN">
  <data key="d0">ORGANIZATION</data>
  <data key="d1">The Bank of Wisconsin is a financial institution that issued the credit card account #543298760192XXXX51. They also conducted an account review inquiry on the individual's credit report in June 2019, from their location in Big City, WI.</data>
  <data key="d2">2</data>
</node>
<node id="INDIVIDUAL CONSUMER">
  <data key="d0">PERSON</data>
  <data key="d1">The unnamed individual whose credit report information is presented. This person is responsible for the credit card account #543298760192XXXX51, has a balance of $4,252, and is paying minimum payments, which will take 17 years and 9 months to clear the debt and incur $6,731 in interest.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="CREDIT CARD ACCOUNT 543298760192XXXX51">
  <data key="d0">FINANCIAL_PRODUCT</data>
  <data key="d1">A revolving credit card account held by the Individual Consumer with the Bank of Wisconsin. It was opened on June 1, 2008, has a credit limit of $10,000, a high balance of $9,869, and a current balance of $4,252 as of August 31, 2019. The account has a 22% APR and received a "30 days past due" rating in February 2019.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="CURRENT BALANCE">
  <data key="d0">FINANCIAL_CONCEPT</data>
  <data key="d1">The present amount of money owed on the credit card account, which is $4,252 as of August 31, 2019.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="CREDIT LIMIT">
  <data key="d0">FINANCIAL_CONCEPT</data>
  <data key="d1">The maximum amount of credit that a lender or financial institution extends to a borrower on a specific account, which is a factor in calculating credit utilization rate.</data>
  <data key="d2">7</data>
</node>
<node id="HIGH BALANCE">
  <data key="d0">FINANCIAL_CONCEPT</data>
  <data key="d1">The largest recorded debt balance on the credit card account at any point, which was $9,869.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="ANNUAL PERCENTAGE RATE">
  <data key="d0">FINANCIAL_CONCEPT</data>
  <data key="d1">The full term for APR, representing the yearly cost of borrowing money on a credit card or loan, expressed as a percentage.</data>
  <data key="d2">2</data>
</node>
<node id="MINIMUM PAYMENT">
  <data key="d0">FINANCIAL_CONCEPT</data>
  <data key="d1">The lowest amount the Individual Consumer is required to pay on their credit card bill each month, calculated as the greater of $25 or the sum of 1% of the principal balance, finance charges, and fees.</data>
  <data key="d2">2</data>
</node>
<node id="INTEREST PAYMENT">
  <data key="d0">FINANCIAL_CONCEPT</data>
  <data key="d1">The cost of borrowing money, estimated at $6,731 over 17 years and 9 months if only minimum payments are made on the credit card account.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="LATE FEES">
  <data key="d0">RISK</data>
  <data key="d1">Charges incurred for failing to return borrowed items on time or for late payments, which should be avoided to save money.</data>
  <data key="d2">16</data>
</node>
<node id="CREDIT REPORT">
  <data key="d0">FINANCIAL_PRODUCT</data>
  <data key="d1">A detailed summary of an individual's credit history, including payment status, account information, and inquiries, used by lenders to assess creditworthiness. This document itself is an example of a credit report.</data>
  <data key="d2">20</data>
</node>
<node id="AUTO LOAN STORE">
