  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="LITTLETOWN, MI">
  <data key="d0">GEO</data>
  <data key="d1">A city in Michigan that is the location of the EZ Loan Store, associated with a promotional credit inquiry.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="HARD INQUIRIES">
  <data key="d0">ACTION</data>
  <data key="d1">Requests made by lenders to view a consumer's credit report when that consumer has applied for new credit. These inquiries typically remain on the credit report for two years and may negatively affect credit scores.</data>
  <data key="d2">2</data>
</node>
<node id="SOFT INQUIRIES">
  <data key="d0">ACTION</data>
  <data key="d1">Reviews of a consumer's credit file that occur without the consumer applying for new credit, such as existing account reviews, promotional offers, or personal credit report requests. These do not affect credit scores.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="CREDIT SCORES">
  <data key="d0">FINANCIAL_CONCEPT</data>
  <data key="d1">A numerical rating derived from the information in an individual's credit reports, used by lenders to evaluate creditworthiness and the likelihood of loan repayment. Errors on credit reports can negatively affect these scores.</data>
  <data key="d2">19</data>
</node>
<node id="AUTHORIZED USER">
  <data key="d0">PERSON</data>
  <data key="d1">A person who is allowed to use a credit card account but is not legally responsible for making payments. The account's payment status can appear on both the authorized user's and the primary owner's credit reports.</data>
  <data key="d2">8</data>
</node>
<node id="CHAPTER 7 BANKRUPTCY">
  <data key="d0">EVENT</data>
  <data key="d1">A legal proceeding in which a consumer's non-exempt assets are liquidated to pay off creditors, and most remaining eligible debts are discharged. This event is recorded in the public records section of a credit report.</data>
  <data key="d2">5</data>
</node>
<node id="CHAPTER 13 BANKRUPTCY">
  <data key="d0">EVENT</data>
  <data key="d1">A legal process where a consumer establishes a court-arranged payment plan using future income to pay creditors, with remaining eligible debts discharged upon the plan's completion, and which is noted in the public records section of a credit report.</data>
  <data key="d2">4</data>
</node>
<node id="PAST DUE RATING (30 DAYS)">
  <data key="d0">FINANCIAL_CONCEPT</data>
  <data key="d1">A negative credit rating indicating that a payment on an account was 30 days late, as shown for the credit card account in February 2019.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="YOUR MONEY, YOUR GOALS TOOLKIT">
  <data key="d0">FINANCIAL_CONCEPT</data>
  <data key="d1">A financial empowerment toolkit developed by the Consumer Financial Protection Bureau, aimed at helping people living with low incomes to manage money, credit, and debt, and to choose appropriate financial products.</data>
  <data key="d2">56</data>
</node>
