  <data key="d2">4</data>
</node>
<node id="PAYMENT">
  <data key="d0">FINANCIAL_CONCEPT</data>
  <data key="d1">An amount of money paid regularly to reduce a debt. Strategies involve paying more than the minimum payment to accelerate debt reduction.</data>
  <data key="d2">5</data>
</node>
<node id="APPLICATION">
  <data key="d0">FINANCIAL_PRODUCT</data>
  <data key="d1">A formal request, typically a document or form, submitted by a borrower to a lender when seeking a loan.</data>
  <data key="d2">2</data>
</node>
<node id="CAR">
  <data key="d0">FINANCIAL_PRODUCT</data>
  <data key="d1">A vehicle owned by an individual, which is considered an asset but typically not a liquid asset when determining public benefits eligibility</data>
  <data key="d2">9</data>
</node>
<node id="AUTO LOAN">
  <data key="d0">FINANCIAL_PRODUCT</data>
  <data key="d1">A type of loan used to finance the purchase of an automobile. The terms of an auto loan can be negotiated, and its total cost is influenced by factors like credit score and APR.</data>
  <data key="d2">14</data>
</node>
<node id="LEASE">
  <data key="d0">FINANCIAL_PRODUCT</data>
  <data key="d1">A contractual agreement by which one party grants another party the use of an asset, such as a home, for a specified period in exchange for regular payments, and can serve as proof of residence.</data>
  <data key="d2">4</data>
</node>
<node id="CAR'S TOTAL VALUE">
  <data key="d0">FINANCIAL_CONCEPT</data>
  <data key="d1">The complete market worth or appraisal of a car, which determines the maximum amount that can be borrowed in an auto title loan.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="30-DAY SINGLE PAYMENT LOAN">
  <data key="d0">FINANCIAL_PRODUCT</data>
  <data key="d1">A specific type of auto title loan that requires the full principal and interest to be repaid in a single payment within 30 days.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="SINGLE PAYMENT">
  <data key="d0">FINANCIAL_CONCEPT</data>
  <data key="d1">A repayment method where the entire loan amount, including principal and fees, is paid off in one lump sum.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="BALANCE DUE">
  <data key="d0">FINANCIAL_CONCEPT</data>
  <data key="d1">The outstanding amount of money that a borrower still owes on a loan or debt, typically after some payments have been made or a car is repossessed.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="SALE PRICE">
  <data key="d0">FINANCIAL_CONCEPT</data>
  <data key="d1">The amount of money received when a repossessed item, such as a car, is sold, typically at auction.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="DIFFERENCE">
  <data key="d0">FINANCIAL_CONCEPT</data>
  <data key="d1">The remaining amount a borrower may still owe if the sale price of a repossessed car does not fully cover the balance due.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="FURNITURE">
  <data key="d0">FINANCIAL_PRODUCT</data>
  <data key="d1">Household items like chairs, tables, and beds, which are examples of consumer goods available through rent-to-own arrangements.</data>
  <data key="d2">2</data>
</node>
<node id="ELECTRONICS">
  <data key="d0">FINANCIAL_PRODUCT</data>
  <data key="d1">Electronic devices such as televisions, computers, and sound systems, which are examples of consumer goods available through rent-to-own arrangements.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="APPLIANCES">
  <data key="d0">FINANCIAL_PRODUCT</data>
  <data key="d1">Household machines like refrigerators, washing machines, and ovens, which are examples of consumer goods available through rent-to-own arrangements.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="OUTSTANDING BALANCE">
  <data key="d0">FINANCIAL_CONCEPT</data>
  <data key="d1">The remaining amount of a debt or bill that has not yet been paid, after accounting for any previous payments or credits.</data>
  <data key="d2">2</data>
</node>
<node id="TERM">
  <data key="d0">FINANCIAL_CONCEPT</data>
  <data key="d1">The specified duration or period for which a loan or contract is valid.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="CONTRACT">
  <data key="d0">FINANCIAL_PRODUCT</data>
  <data key="d1">A legally binding agreement, often for financial products or services, which should be thoroughly understood before signing and should not contain blank spaces.</data>
  <data key="d2">2</data>
</node>
<node id="TAKE BACK">
  <data key="d0">ACTION</data>
  <data key="d1">The act of a rent-to-own company reclaiming possession of an item, typically due to missed payments.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="LOAN PAYMENT">
  <data key="d0">FINANCIAL_CONCEPT</data>
  <data key="d1">A scheduled remittance of money towards the repayment of a loan, which if overdue, may allow a bank to collect directly from an account via set-off.</data>
  <data key="d2">3</data>
</node>
<node id="FOOD">
  <data key="d0">FINANCIAL_PRODUCT</data>
