  <data key="d2">4</data>
</node>
<node id="PAST DUE AMOUNT">
  <data key="d0">FINANCIAL_CONCEPT</data>
  <data key="d1">An amount of money that has not been paid by its due date, which then typically accrues fees and becomes a form of debt.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="CASH">
  <data key="d0">FINANCIAL_PRODUCT</data>
  <data key="d1">Physical currency (paper or coin) minted by the U.S. government, offering widespread acceptance and easy access, but susceptible to loss, theft, impulsive spending, and difficult to track for budgeting and tax purposes.</data>
  <data key="d2">17</data>
</node>
<node id="PREPAID CARD">
  <data key="d0">FINANCIAL_PRODUCT</data>
  <data key="d1">A financial product used for spending or withdrawing funds, which may incur fees for various actions like cancellation, bill payment, or money transfer. It offers certain rights and protections, especially when registered, and can be used for wages or government benefits. It may include features like a savings wallet.</data>
  <data key="d2">30</data>
</node>
<node id="ACCOUNT BALANCES">
  <data key="d0">FINANCIAL_CONCEPT</data>
