<node id="AUTO INSURANCE POLICY">
  <data key="d0">FINANCIAL_PRODUCT</data>
  <data key="d1">An Auto Insurance Policy is a formal contract between an individual and an insurance provider that outlines the terms, coverages, and conditions of car insurance.</data>
  <data key="d2">3</data>
</node>
<node id="INSURANCE POLICY">
  <data key="d0">FINANCIAL_CONCEPT</data>
  <data key="d1">An insurance policy is a contract between an insurance company and an insured individual, outlining the terms, conditions, coverages, and deductibles that apply to the protection provided.</data>
  <data key="d2">2</data>
</node>
<node id="COLLISION">
  <data key="d0">FINANCIAL_CONCEPT</data>
  <data key="d1">A type of auto insurance coverage that pays for damage to your car from a collision with another vehicle or object.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="COMPREHENSIVE">
  <data key="d0">FINANCIAL_CONCEPT</data>
  <data key="d1">A type of auto insurance coverage that pays for damage to your car from non-collision events like theft, vandalism, or natural disasters.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="DEDUCTIBLES">
  <data key="d0">FINANCIAL_CONCEPT</data>
  <data key="d1">The amount of money the insured must pay out-of-pocket for a claim before their insurance company pays the rest. Higher deductibles typically lower the premium but increase the immediate cost if a loss occurs.</data>
  <data key="d2">2</data>
</node>
<node id="TELEMATICS">
  <data key="d0">FINANCIAL_CONCEPT</data>
