  <data key="d1">"A medical doctor specializing in children's health, whose contact information is recommended to be included in the Emergency Financial First Aid Kit.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;MEDICAL SPECIALIST&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"A doctor with expertise in a specific area of medicine (e.g., dentist, optometrist), whose contact information is recommended to be included in the Emergency Financial First Aid Kit.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;DENTIST&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"A healthcare professional specializing in oral health, whose contact information may be included as a medical specialist.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;OPTOMETRIST&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"A healthcare professional specializing in eye care, whose contact information may be included as a medical specialist.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="DIRECT MARKETING ASSOCIATION (DMA)">
  <data key="d0">ORGANIZATION</data>
  <data key="d1">An organization that manages direct mail marketers' lists, allowing individuals to register to remove their names and reduce unsolicited mail.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="DO NOT CALL REGISTRY">
  <data key="d0">ORGANIZATION</data>
  <data key="d1">A national registry that allows individuals to remove their phone numbers from telemarketers' lists to stop unwanted calls.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="U.S.">
  <data key="d0">GEO</data>
  <data key="d1">A country where tens of millions of people are affected by identity theft, fraud, and data breaches each year.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="PHISHING">
  <data key="d0">RISK</data>
  <data key="d1">A fraudulent method where scammers attempt to acquire sensitive personal information by impersonating trustworthy entities, often through fake emails or websites.</data>
  <data key="d2">2</data>
</node>
<node id="DATA BREACHES">
  <data key="d0">RISK</data>
  <data key="d1">Security incidents where sensitive personal information is exposed to unauthorized parties, affecting millions in the U.S. annually.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="CREDIT FILE">
  <data key="d0">FINANCIAL_CONCEPT</data>
  <data key="d1">The compilation of an individual's credit history and personal data maintained by credit reporting companies, which can be protected by freezes or fraud alerts.</data>
  <data key="d2">2</data>
</node>
<node id="FRAUD ALERT">
  <data key="d0">FINANCIAL_CONCEPT</data>
  <data key="d1">A notice placed on a credit file that advises lenders to take extra steps to verify identity before granting new credit, as a preventative measure against identity theft.</data>
  <data key="d2">2</data>
</node>
<node id="PRESCREENED OFFERS">
  <data key="d0">FINANCIAL_CONCEPT</data>
  <data key="d1">Unsolicited invitations for credit or insurance that are sent to consumers, which can be intercepted by thieves and used for fraudulent applications.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="CHECKING CREDIT REPORT">
  <data key="d0">ACTION</data>
  <data key="d1">The proactive step of regularly reviewing one's credit report from all three nationwide credit reporting companies to detect errors or fraudulent activity.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="FREEZING CREDIT FILE">
  <data key="d0">ACTION</data>
  <data key="d1">A security measure that restricts access to an individual's credit report, making it difficult for identity thieves to open new accounts in their name.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="PUTTING A FRAUD ALERT ON CREDIT FILE">
  <data key="d0">ACTION</data>
  <data key="d1">The act of placing a temporary notice on a credit file that requires businesses to verify a person's identity before extending credit, as a safeguard against identity theft.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="OPTING OUT OF PRESCREENED OFFERS">
  <data key="d0">ACTION</data>
  <data key="d1">The process of removing one's name from mailing lists for unsolicited credit and insurance offers, thereby reducing the risk of these offers being intercepted and used fraudulently.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="REGISTERING WITH DIRECT MARKETING ASSOCIATION">
  <data key="d0">ACTION</data>
  <data key="d1">The action of signing up with the DMA to reduce the amount of direct mail received, which helps limit opportunities for thieves to steal information.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="REGISTERING WITH DO NOT CALL REGISTRY">
  <data key="d0">ACTION</data>
  <data key="d1">The act of adding one's phone number to a federal registry to prevent telemarketers from making unwanted sales calls.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="USING A SHREDDER">
  <data key="d0">ACTION</data>
  <data key="d1">The practice of destroying documents containing sensitive identifying or account information by cutting them into tiny pieces before disposal, to prevent identity theft.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="EFFAK">
  <data key="d0">FINANCIAL_CONCEPT</data>
  <data key="d1">An acronym for Emergency Financial First Aid Kit, referring to a collection of important financial and personal documents and information to be used in emergencies, especially if stolen or illegally accessed.</data>
  <data key="d2">2</data>
</node>
<node id="FEMA">
  <data key="d0">ORGANIZATION</data>
  <data key="d1">The Federal Emergency Management Agency, a government agency and the newest member of a group. It has rights for and distributes the Emergency Financial First Aid Kit and is a component of the Department of Homeland Security.</data>
  <data key="d2">8</data>
</node>
<node id="DISASTER">
  <data key="d0">RISK</data>
  <data key="d1">An event that can cause damage to a home, potentially making it uninhabitable, but does not relieve mortgage payment obligations.</data>
  <data key="d2">4</data>
</node>
<node id="CENTERS FOR DISEASE CONTROL AND PREVENTION">
  <data key="d0">ORGANIZATION</data>
  <data key="d1">A government agency that maintains a state-by-state contact list for obtaining copies of vital records such as birth, adoption, death, marriage, and divorce certificates.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="SOCIAL SECURITY ADMINISTRATION">
  <data key="d0">ORGANIZATION</data>
  <data key="d1">A government agency that provides assistance for obtaining new or replacement Social Security cards.</data>
  <data key="d2">2</data>
</node>
<node id="NATIONAL PASSPORT INFORMATION CENTER">
  <data key="d0">ORGANIZATION</data>
  <data key="d1">The National Passport Information Center provides information and assistance for applying for and renewing passports.</data>
  <data key="d2">3</data>
</node>
<node id="U.S. DEPARTMENT OF STATE">
  <data key="d0">ORGANIZATION</data>
  <data key="d1">The United States federal department responsible for foreign affairs, which provides information and services related to passports via its website www.travel.state.gov/passports.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="U.S. CITIZENSHIP AND IMMIGRATION SERVICES">
  <data key="d0">ORGANIZATION</data>
  <data key="d1">A government agency that provides information about applying for, renewing, and replacing Green Cards, and naturalization documents.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="PASSPORT">
  <data key="d0">FINANCIAL_PRODUCT</data>
  <data key="d1">An official identification document issued by a government, listed in the EFFAK checklists, for which application and renewal information is available from the National Passport Information Center and the U.S. Department of State.</data>
  <data key="d2">2</data>
</node>
<node id="GREEN CARD">
  <data key="d0">FINANCIAL_PRODUCT</data>
  <data key="d1">An official document evidencing permanent residency status in the U.S., listed in the EFFAK checklists, with information on its application, renewal, and replacement available from U.S. Citizenship and Immigration Services.</data>
  <data key="d2">2</data>
</node>
<node id="NATURALIZATION DOCUMENTS">
  <data key="d0">FINANCIAL_PRODUCT</data>
  <data key="d1">Official documents serving as acceptable proof of U.S. citizenship for individuals not born in the United States, with information available from U.S. Citizenship and Immigration Services.</data>
  <data key="d2">2</data>
</node>
<node id="BIRTH CERTIFICATE(S)/ADOPTION PAPERS/CHILD CUSTODY DOCUMENTS">
  <data key="d0">FINANCIAL_PRODUCT</data>
  <data key="d1">Vital legal documents proving identity, parentage, or guardianship, listed in the EFFAK checklists, obtainable from state health or social services offices.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="MARRIAGE LICENSE">
  <data key="d0">FINANCIAL_PRODUCT</data>
  <data key="d1">A vital legal document proving marriage, listed in the EFFAK checklists, obtainable from state health or social services offices.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="DIVORCE DECREE">
  <data key="d0">FINANCIAL_PRODUCT</data>
  <data key="d1">A vital legal document proving divorce, listed in the EFFAK checklists, obtainable from state health or social services offices.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="SOCIAL SECURITY CARD(S)">
  <data key="d0">FINANCIAL_PRODUCT</data>
  <data key="d1">An official identification document issued by the Social Security Administration, listed in the EFFAK checklists, for which replacement cards can be obtained from the SSA.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="CHILD IDENTITY CARDS/DENTAL RECORDS/DNA SWABS">
