  <data key="d0">ACTION</data>
  <data key="d1">The activity of looking for employment opportunities, as suggested by usa.gov/find-a-job.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="ENROLL IN HEALTH INSURANCE">
  <data key="d0">ACTION</data>
  <data key="d1">The process of signing up for a health insurance plan, as suggested by healthcare.gov.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="CONTACT YOUR STATE ATTORNEY GENERAL’S OFFICE">
  <data key="d0">ACTION</data>
  <data key="d1">The act of reaching out to the state attorney general's office for assistance or information regarding complaints.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="ALIGNING EXPENSES WITH INCOME">
  <data key="d0">ACTION</data>
  <data key="d1">The main objective of the financial management activity described, which is to create a better match between money coming in and money going out.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="INCOME SOURCES">
  <data key="d0">FINANCIAL_CONCEPT</data>
  <data key="d1">The various origins from which an individual receives money, such as jobs and benefits, which should be entered on the calendar.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="FEDERAL PROTECTIONS">
  <data key="d0">FINANCIAL_CONCEPT</data>
  <data key="d1">A set of legal rights and requirements under federal law that apply to consumers sending money abroad through remittance transfer providers, covering information disclosure, cancellation, and error resolution.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="MONEY TRANSFER">
  <data key="d0">FINANCIAL_PRODUCT</data>
  <data key="d1">A financial service involving the transmission of funds from a consumer in the United States to a person or company in a foreign country, subject to federal protections.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="CANCELLATION RIGHT">
  <data key="d0">FINANCIAL_CONCEPT</data>
  <data key="d1">A consumer's legal right to cancel a money transfer transaction, typically within 30 minutes after paying or at least three business days before a scheduled transfer.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="ERROR RESOLUTION RIGHT">
  <data key="d0">FINANCIAL_CONCEPT</data>
  <data key="d1">A consumer's legal right to have mistakes related to a money transfer investigated and resolved by the remittance provider, typically within 90 days of notification.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="SURPRISES">
  <data key="d0">RISK</data>
  <data key="d1">Unexpected or undisclosed issues, often financial, related to international money transfers that federal protections aim to prevent or eliminate for consumers.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="MONTHLY SERVICE FEE">
  <data key="d0">FINANCIAL_CONCEPT</data>
  <data key="d1">A Monthly Service Fee is a recurring charge levied by financial institutions for the maintenance and use of certain financial products, such as a checking account.</data>
  <data key="d2">2</data>
</node>
<node id="SCHEDULED PAYMENT">
  <data key="d0">ACTION</data>
  <data key="d1">A pre-arranged payment that is set to occur at a future date, for which account holders should ensure they have sufficient funds to avoid alerts or fees.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="STUDENT ACCOUNT">
  <data key="d0">FINANCIAL_PRODUCT</data>
  <data key="d1">A type of checking account specifically designed for students, often featuring a low minimum balance requirement and reduced or waived monthly service fees.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="SENIOR ACCOUNT">
  <data key="d0">FINANCIAL_PRODUCT</data>
  <data key="d1">A type of checking account tailored for senior citizens, typically offering a low minimum balance requirement and often reduced or waived monthly service fees.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="BASIC CHECKING ACCOUNT">
  <data key="d0">FINANCIAL_PRODUCT</data>
  <data key="d1">A straightforward checking account that typically has a low minimum balance requirement and a limited number of free checks and withdrawals, often resulting in lower fees.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="FIGURE OUT CREDIT UTILIZATION RATE">
  <data key="d0">ACTION</data>
  <data key="d1">The process of calculating a consumer's credit utilization rate based on their charged amount and credit limit, as described by a given formula.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="LOWERING CREDIT UTILIZATION RATE GOAL">
  <data key="d0">ACTION</data>
  <data key="d1">The objective or target set by a consumer to reduce their credit utilization rate to a specific percentage, often recommended to be 25% or less.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="PAY DOWN CREDIT CARD BALANCE">
  <data key="d0">ACTION</data>
  <data key="d1">The act of making payments to reduce the outstanding amount owed on a credit card, which can help in managing credit utilization and scores.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="PLAN FOR REPAYMENT">
  <data key="d0">ACTION</data>
  <data key="d1">A structured strategy developed to pay back outstanding debts and manage monthly bills and expenses.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="RIGHTS IN DEBT COLLECTION">
  <data key="d0">FINANCIAL_CONCEPT</data>
  <data key="d1">Legal entitlements and protections afforded to consumers when interacting with debt collectors or undergoing the debt collection process.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="RISKS OF NOT PAYING">
  <data key="d0">RISK</data>
  <data key="d1">The potential negative consequences, such as late fees, repossession, negative credit entries, or legal action, that can arise from failing to pay bills or meet financial obligations.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="THINGS I NEED FOR A JOB">
  <data key="d0">FINANCIAL_CONCEPT</data>
  <data key="d1">A category of essential expenses required to maintain employment, including transportation, equipment, uniforms, and childcare.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="MONTHLY AMOUNT OF EACH BILL">
  <data key="d0">FINANCIAL_CONCEPT</data>
  <data key="d1">The specific sum of money owed for a bill on a recurring monthly basis, which may be estimated if it changes frequently.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="THINGS I NEED FOR HOUSING">
  <data key="d0">FINANCIAL_CONCEPT</data>
  <data key="d1">A category of essential expenses required to maintain a place of residence, such as rent, mortgage, property taxes, and utility bills.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="UTILITIES BEING CUT OFF">
  <data key="d0">RISK</data>
  <data key="d1">The risk that essential services like gas, electricity, water, garbage, or sewer will be disconnected due to non-payment of associated bills.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="GAS, ELECTRIC">
  <data key="d0">FINANCIAL_PRODUCT</data>
  <data key="d1">Specific utility services that provide energy for heating, cooling, and power, requiring regular payments.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="WATER, GARBAGE, SEWER">
  <data key="d0">FINANCIAL_PRODUCT</data>
  <data key="d1">Specific utility and waste management services essential for household functioning and sanitation, requiring regular payments.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="CREDIT CARD PAYMENT">
  <data key="d0">FINANCIAL_CONCEPT</data>
  <data key="d1">A specific payment made towards an outstanding balance on a credit card, which if missed, can incur late fees and negative credit impacts.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="OBLIGATIONS I HAVE TO PAY">
  <data key="d0">FINANCIAL_CONCEPT</data>
  <data key="d1">A general category encompassing all financial commitments and debts that an individual is responsible for paying, including credit cards, loans, and court-ordered obligations.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="PUTTING GOALS INTO ACTION TOOL">
  <data key="d0">ACTION</data>
  <data key="d1">A tool within the toolkit designed to help individuals transform their SMART goals into an easy-to-follow action plan by breaking them into steps, identifying necessary resources, and setting deadlines.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="DR. GAIL MATTHEWS">
  <data key="d0">PERSON</data>
  <data key="d1">A researcher from Dominican University of California whose work supports the claim that people who write down specific goals are more likely to achieve them.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="DOMINICAN UNIVERSITY OF CALIFORNIA">
  <data key="d0">ORGANIZATION</data>
  <data key="d1">An academic institution where Dr. Gail Matthews conducted research on the effectiveness of writing down specific goals.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="FEBRUARY 2020">
  <data key="d0">EVENT</data>
  <data key="d1">The specified date as of which FICA and Medicare contributions are accurate.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="GARNISHING YOUR WAGES">
  <data key="d0">ACTION</data>
  <data key="d1">The act of legally withholding a portion of an individual's earnings to satisfy a debt.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="SUES">
  <data key="d0">ACTION</data>
  <data key="d1">The legal action initiated by a creditor against a debtor for unpaid debts.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="REPAID">
  <data key="d0">ACTION</data>
  <data key="d1">The act of settling a financial obligation by returning borrowed money or making payments for a debt.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="PAY OFF THE DEBT">
  <data key="d0">ACTION</data>
  <data key="d1">The act of fully satisfying a financial obligation by making the final required payments.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="WAGE GARNISHMENT ORDER">
  <data key="d0">FINANCIAL_PRODUCT</data>
  <data key="d1">A legal document issued by a court or administrative body that directs an employer to withhold a portion of an employee's wages for debt repayment.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="ADMINISTRATIVE PROCEEDING">
  <data key="d0">EVENT</data>
  <data key="d1">A non-judicial process conducted by a government agency to determine and establish amounts due for obligations like child support, potentially leading to garnishment without a court order.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="FEDERAL TAXES">
  <data key="d0">FINANCIAL_CONCEPT</data>
  <data key="d1">Mandatory financial charges levied by the federal government, deducted from wages.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="STATE TAXES">
  <data key="d0">FINANCIAL_CONCEPT</data>
  <data key="d1">Mandatory financial charges levied by state governments, deducted from wages.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="WEEKLY EARNINGS">
  <data key="d0">FINANCIAL_CONCEPT</data>
  <data key="d1">The total amount of money earned by an individual within a week, used in calculating garnishment limits.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="SUPPORT PAYMENTS">
  <data key="d0">FINANCIAL_PRODUCT</data>
  <data key="d1">A general category of financial aid provided to dependants or former spouses, such as child support or spousal support payments.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="GOVERNMENT DEBTS">
  <data key="d0">FINANCIAL_CONCEPT</data>
  <data key="d1">Financial obligations owed to a governmental entity, which can often be collected through garnishment or tax refund offsets.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="FEDERAL AGENCY">
  <data key="d0">ORGANIZATION</data>
  <data key="d1">A department, agency, or other entity of the federal government, to which debts may be owed and which can initiate tax refund offsets.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="PRIVATE CREDITOR">
  <data key="d0">ORGANIZATION</data>
  <data key="d1">A non-governmental entity to whom money is owed, whose claims generally cannot be garnished from federal tax refunds directly but may be from deposited refunds.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="IRS.GOV">
  <data key="d0">ORGANIZATION</data>
  <data key="d1">The official website of the Internal Revenue Service, providing information on tax refund garnishments and offsets.</data>
  <data key="d2">2</data>
</node>
<node id="TAX REFUND GARNISHMENTS">
  <data key="d0">EVENT</data>
  <data key="d1">The action of reducing or withholding a tax refund to satisfy an outstanding debt, often referred to as an offset by the IRS.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="DEBIT CARDS">
  <data key="d0">FINANCIAL_PRODUCT</data>
  <data key="d1">Payment cards linked directly to a bank account, which should be physically destroyed (cut up) when old or cancelled to prevent fraudulent use.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="FINANCIAL ACCOUNT">
  <data key="d0">FINANCIAL_PRODUCT</data>
  <data key="d1">A general term for various types of accounts held at financial institutions, which identity thieves can fraudulently open or put charges on using stolen personal information.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="PRACTICING ONLINE SECURITY">
  <data key="d0">ACTION</data>
  <data key="d1">The action of implementing safeguards and cautious behaviors when using the internet to protect personal information and prevent identity theft.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="LIMITING ACCESS TO PERSONAL INFORMATION">
  <data key="d0">ACTION</data>
  <data key="d1">The action of restricting who can obtain or view one's private data, both online and offline, to reduce the risk of identity theft.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="AVOIDING CARRYING SOCIAL SECURITY NUMBER IN WALLET">
  <data key="d0">ACTION</data>
  <data key="d1">The action of refraining from keeping one's Social Security card or number in a wallet or purse, opting instead to store it safely at home.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="AVOIDING GIVING PERSONAL INFORMATION TO UNKNOWN CALLERS">
  <data key="d0">ACTION</data>
  <data key="d1">The action of refusing to provide sensitive personal details to unsolicited callers, even if they claim to be from a trusted financial institution, to prevent scams and identity theft.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="CUTTING UP OLD CARDS">
  <data key="d0">ACTION</data>
  <data key="d1">The physical act of destroying old or cancelled credit cards and debit cards by cutting them into tiny pieces before disposal to prevent unauthorized individuals from using their information.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="LIMITING SOCIAL SECURITY NUMBER DISCLOSURE">
  <data key="d0">ACTION</data>
  <data key="d1">The action of providing one's Social Security number only when it is absolutely necessary and legally required, to minimize its exposure to potential thieves.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="PROTECTING MOTHER'S MAIDEN NAME">
  <data key="d0">ACTION</data>
  <data key="d1">The action of safeguarding one's mother's maiden name, which is often used as a security question for identity verification, especially by not publishing it on social media.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="MEMORIZING PASSWORDS">
  <data key="d0">ACTION</data>
  <data key="d1">The action of committing passwords to memory rather than writing them down, as a practice to enhance online security and prevent unauthorized access to accounts.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="GUARDING IDENTIFYING INFORMATION">
  <data key="d0">ACTION</data>
  <data key="d1">The comprehensive action of carefully protecting one's personal and identifying information from unauthorized access or theft through various security practices.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="SHARING IDENTIFYING INFORMATION CAREFULLY">
  <data key="d0">ACTION</data>
  <data key="d1">The action of only disclosing identifying information to individuals or entities that are trusted and for whom there is a legitimate reason for sharing the data.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="SEARCHING FOR SCAM INFORMATION ONLINE">
  <data key="d0">ACTION</data>
  <data key="d1">The action of actively looking for information on the internet, such as on government scam alert websites, to verify the legitimacy of potential scams.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="HANDLING IDENTITY THEFT">
  <data key="d0">ACTION</data>
  <data key="d1">The procedural steps taken by an individual after their identity has been stolen, including reporting the theft and taking measures to mitigate damage and restore their identity.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="FEDERAL OR STATE AGENCY">
  <data key="d0">ORGANIZATION</data>
  <data key="d1">A government entity to which certain debts may be owed, leading to the offset of federal tax refunds.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="PRIVATE CREDITOR OR COLLECTOR">
  <data key="d0">ORGANIZATION</data>
  <data key="d1">An entity or individual seeking repayment of a debt that cannot garnish federal tax refunds directly but may garnish funds once they are deposited into a bank account.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="BANK OR CREDIT UNION ACCOUNT">
  <data key="d0">FINANCIAL_PRODUCT</data>
  <data key="d1">A financial account where funds, including federal tax refunds and protected benefits, are held, potentially subject to garnishment or set-off.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="SOCIAL SECURITY OR VETERANS' BENEFITS">
  <data key="d0">FINANCIAL_PRODUCT</data>
  <data key="d1">Federal payments provided to eligible individuals, which are often protected from garnishment, especially when directly deposited into an account.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="DEPOSITOR AGREEMENT">
  <data key="d0">FINANCIAL_CONCEPT</data>
  <data key="d1">The legal contract between a bank and its customer, outlining the terms and conditions of the bank account, including provisions for set-offs.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="FEDERAL AND STATE LAW">
  <data key="d0">FINANCIAL_CONCEPT</data>
  <data key="d1">The body of legal rules and statutes at federal and state levels that determine what funds are protected or exempt from garnishment or set-off.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="UNEMPLOYMENT COMPENSATION">
  <data key="d0">FINANCIAL_PRODUCT</data>
  <data key="d1">Benefits provided by state governments to eligible individuals who are unemployed, which some states protect from set-off.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="JUDGE">
  <data key="d0">PERSON</data>
  <data key="d1">A public official appointed to decide cases in a court of law, who determines if money should be protected from garnishment based on legal exemptions and source of income.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="CONSUMERFINANCE.GOV/ASKCFPB/1549">
  <data key="d0">ORGANIZATION</data>
  <data key="d1">A specific webpage provided by the Consumer Financial Protection Bureau (CFPB) for individuals to find legal aid lawyers in their state.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="SERVICEMEMBERS">
  <data key="d0">PERSON</data>
  <data key="d1">Individuals actively serving in the armed forces who are entitled to legal assistance through their Judge Advocate General’s (JAG) office.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="JUDGE ADVOCATE GENERAL’S (JAG) OFFICE">
  <data key="d0">ORGANIZATION</data>
  <data key="d1">A military legal office that provides legal services and advice to Servicemembers.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="LEGALASSISTANCE.LAW.AF.MIL/">
  <data key="d0">ORGANIZATION</data>
  <data key="d1">A website for Servicemembers to locate their local Judge Advocate General’s (JAG) office for legal assistance.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="LAWYER REFERRAL SERVICE">
  <data key="d0">ORGANIZATION</data>
  <data key="d1">A service that connects individuals with lawyers experienced in specific legal fields, such as garnishment and debt collection.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="PHYSICIAN">
  <data key="d0">PERSON</data>
  <data key="d1">A medical professional whose contact information, and potentially business card or recent paperwork, should be included in the EFFAK.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="PEDIATRICIAN">
  <data key="d0">PERSON</data>
  <data key="d1">A medical doctor specializing in child healthcare, whose contact information should be included in the EFFAK.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="MEDICAL SPECIALIST">
  <data key="d0">PERSON</data>
  <data key="d1">Healthcare providers such as dentists or optometrists, whose contact information should be included in the EFFAK.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="HEALTH INSURANCE ID CARD">
  <data key="d0">FINANCIAL_PRODUCT</data>
  <data key="d1">An identification card for health insurance, a copy of which should be stored in the EFFAK and can be obtained from the insurance provider.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="VETERAN HEALTH IDENTIFICATION CARD">
  <data key="d0">FINANCIAL_PRODUCT</data>
  <data key="d1">An identification card for veterans accessing health services, a copy of which should be stored in the EFFAK and can be obtained from the Department of Veterans Affairs.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="PHARMACY ID CARD">
  <data key="d0">FINANCIAL_PRODUCT</data>
  <data key="d1">An identification card for pharmacy services, a copy of which should be stored in the EFFAK.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="MEDICARE CARD">
  <data key="d0">FINANCIAL_PRODUCT</data>
  <data key="d1">An identification card for the federal health insurance program (Medicare), a copy of which should be stored in the EFFAK.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="MEDICAID CARD">
  <data key="d0">FINANCIAL_PRODUCT</data>
  <data key="d1">An identification card for the state and federal health program (Medicaid), a copy of which should be stored in the EFFAK.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="CAREGIVER AGENCY CONTRACT OR SERVICE AGREEMENT">
  <data key="d0">FINANCIAL_PRODUCT</data>
  <data key="d1">A legal document outlining terms with a caregiver agency, which should be stored in the EFFAK.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="PRESCRIPTIONS">
  <data key="d0">FINANCIAL_PRODUCT</data>
  <data key="d1">Copies of current prescriptions, including those for glasses or pets, which should be kept in the EFFAK.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="MEDICAL EQUIPMENT">
  <data key="d0">FINANCIAL_PRODUCT</data>
  <data key="d1">Equipment such as pacemakers or wheelchairs, for which models, serial numbers, and suppliers should be listed in the EFFAK.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="DISABILITIES DOCUMENTATION">
  <data key="d0">FINANCIAL_PRODUCT</data>
  <data key="d1">Official paperwork providing proof of disabilities, which should be stored in the EFFAK.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="LIVING WILL/POWER OF ATTORNEY (MEDICAL)">
  <data key="d0">FINANCIAL_PRODUCT</data>
  <data key="d1">A legal document explaining medical care preferences in life-threatening situations or designating a medical power of attorney, which should be stored in the EFFAK.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="HEALTH CARE PROVIDER">
  <data key="d0">PERSON</data>
  <data key="d1">A general professional in the medical field with whom one might discuss a living will.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="VETERINARIAN">
  <data key="d0">PERSON</data>
  <data key="d1">An animal healthcare professional whose contact information should be included in the EFFAK.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="PET IMMUNIZATION RECORDS">
  <data key="d0">FINANCIAL_PRODUCT</data>
  <data key="d1">Documents detailing a pet's vaccinations, which should be stored in the EFFAK.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="SERVICE PROVIDER">
  <data key="d0">ORGANIZATION</data>
  <data key="d1">Organizations or individuals offering various services (e.g., utility providers), whose contact information should be kept in the EFFAK.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="MORTGAGE REPRESENTATIVE">
  <data key="d0">PERSON</data>
  <data key="d1">A person representing a lender for mortgage services, whose contact information should be stored in the EFFAK.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="AUDIOLOGIST">
  <data key="d0">PERSON</data>
  <data key="d1">A health care provider specializing in hearing and balance disorders, whose contact information should be kept in the EFFAK.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="KIDNEY DIALYSIS CENTER">
  <data key="d0">ORGANIZATION</data>
  <data key="d1">A medical facility providing kidney dialysis services, whose contact information should be kept in the EFFAK.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="MILITARY BENEFITS REPRESENTATIVE">
  <data key="d0">PERSON</data>
  <data key="d1">The individual responsible for managing one's military benefits, whose contact information should be kept in the EFFAK.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="SOCIAL SERVICES REPRESENTATIVE">
  <data key="d0">PERSON</data>
  <data key="d1">A professional providing assistance with social programs, whose contact information should be kept in the EFFAK.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="AID TO FAMILY PROGRAMS">
  <data key="d0">FINANCIAL_CONCEPT</data>
  <data key="d1">Government or charitable initiatives offering various forms of assistance to families, which a social services representative can assist with.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="LOCAL DISABILITY SERVICE PROVIDER">
  <data key="d0">ORGANIZATION</data>
  <data key="d1">An organization offering local services and support to individuals with disabilities, whose contact information should be kept in the EFFAK.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="CASE MANAGER">
  <data key="d0">PERSON</data>
  <data key="d1">A professional who coordinates care and services for individuals, whose contact information should be kept in the EFFAK.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="ASSISTIVE TECHNOLOGY OR DURABLE MEDICAL EQUIPMENT PROVIDER">
  <data key="d0">ORGANIZATION</data>
  <data key="d1">An organization that supplies equipment for individuals with disabilities or for long-term medical care, whose contact information should be kept in the EFFAK.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="BANKING INSTITUTION">
  <data key="d0">ORGANIZATION</data>
  <data key="d1">A financial organization such as a bank or credit union, whose contact information should be kept in the EFFAK.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="NEIGHBORHOOD, CIVIC, AND HOUSE OF WORSHIP CONTACTS">
  <data key="d0">ORGANIZATION</data>
  <data key="d1">Community contacts important for support during an emergency, whose information should be kept in the EFFAK.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="LIFE-THREATENING MEDICAL CONDITION">
  <data key="d0">RISK</data>
  <data key="d1">A severe health issue posing immediate danger to life, addressed by documents like a living will.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="FRIENDS AND FAMILY DEBT">
  <data key="d0">FINANCIAL_PRODUCT</data>
  <data key="d1">Money borrowed from friends or family members, representing a personal loan that creates a debt obligation.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="PAST-DUE FEES AND FINES">
  <data key="d0">FINANCIAL_PRODUCT</data>
  <data key="d1">Charges and penalties that have not been paid by their due date, creating a debt obligation.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="MONTHLY PAYMENT AMOUNTS">
  <data key="d0">FINANCIAL_CONCEPT</data>
  <data key="d1">The specific monetary values required to be paid each month towards debts or other financial obligations.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="OWNER (OF DEBT ACCOUNT)">
  <data key="d0">FINANCIAL_CONCEPT</data>
  <data key="d1">The primary individual or entity legally responsible for a debt account.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="MINIMUM PAYMENT AMOUNT">
  <data key="d0">FINANCIAL_CONCEPT</data>
  <data key="d1">The smallest sum of money required to be paid by the due date to keep an account in good standing and avoid penalties.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="PAYOFF DATE">
  <data key="d0">FINANCIAL_CONCEPT</data>
  <data key="d1">The projected or actual date by which a debt will be fully repaid, including all principal and interest.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="PAST-DUE AMOUNTS">
  <data key="d0">FINANCIAL_CONCEPT</data>
  <data key="d1">Specific sums of money that were due but have not yet been paid, indicating a delinquent financial obligation.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="PAYMENT DUE THIS MONTH">
  <data key="d0">FINANCIAL_CONCEPT</data>
  <data key="d1">The specific amount of money required to be paid for a debt within the current billing cycle or month.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="TOTAL AMOUNT LEFT TO PAY">
  <data key="d0">FINANCIAL_CONCEPT</data>
  <data key="d1">The remaining principal balance and any accrued interest or fees on a debt, indicating the total outstanding obligation.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="GATHERING FINANCIAL DOCUMENTS">
  <data key="d0">ACTION</data>
  <data key="d1">The act of collecting bills, loan statements, and credit reports to comprehensively assess one's financial obligations.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="GETTING CREDIT REPORT">
  <data key="d0">ACTION</data>
  <data key="d1">The action of obtaining a copy of one's credit report to review credit history, identify forgotten debts, or check for collections.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="PRIORITIZING PAYMENTS">
  <data key="d0">ACTION</data>
  <data key="d1">The process of deciding which debts or bills to pay first, often based on factors like interest rates, due dates, or the impact on credit.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="TRACKING DEBTS">
  <data key="d0">ACTION</data>
  <data key="d1">The ongoing activity of monitoring all outstanding financial obligations to understand their current status, amounts, and payment schedules.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="LISTING DEBTS">
  <data key="d0">ACTION</data>
  <data key="d1">The initial step of compiling a comprehensive record of all financial obligations, including the creditors and amounts owed.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="TRACKING DEBT GROWTH/SHRINKAGE">
  <data key="d0">ACTION</data>
  <data key="d1">The periodic monitoring of whether the total amount of debt is increasing or decreasing over time, indicating trends in financial management.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="FIGURING OUT DTI">
  <data key="d0">ACTION</data>
  <data key="d1">The process of calculating one's debt-to-income ratio to understand the proportion of gross monthly income allocated to debt payments.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="FINANCIAL BEHAVIOR">
  <data key="d0">FINANCIAL_CONCEPT</data>
  <data key="d1">Financial behavior refers to the actions and habits individuals exhibit concerning their money, influencing their financial outcomes and adherence to plans.</data>
  <data key="d2">2</data>
</node>
<node id="PART 1: WHAT YOU KNOW">
  <data key="d0">FINANCIAL_CONCEPT</data>
  <data key="d1">Part 1: What You Know is a component of the Financial Empowerment Self-Assessment designed to benchmark an individual's financial knowledge and identify areas for improvement.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="PART 2: HOW YOU FEEL">
  <data key="d0">FINANCIAL_CONCEPT</data>
  <data key="d1">Part 2: How You Feel is a component of the Financial Empowerment Self-Assessment aimed at identifying an individual's emotional perspective and feelings about their own financial life.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="PART 3: YOUR EXPERIENCES">
  <data key="d0">FINANCIAL_CONCEPT</data>
  <data key="d1">Part 3: Your Experiences is a component of the Financial Empowerment Self-Assessment that helps individuals identify their familiarity with various financial products and services.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="MONTHLY DEBT PAYMENTS">
  <data key="d0">FINANCIAL_CONCEPT</data>
  <data key="d1">Monthly Debt Payments are the regular, scheduled payments made towards outstanding debts, influencing an individual's overall financial capacity and credit.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="MONEY OWED">
  <data key="d0">FINANCIAL_CONCEPT</data>
  <data key="d1">Money Owed refers to outstanding debts or liabilities that an individual is obligated to repay to another party.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="TAX FILING ASSISTANCE">
  <data key="d0">FINANCIAL_CONCEPT</data>
  <data key="d1">Tax Filing Assistance is support provided to individuals in preparing and submitting their tax returns to relevant authorities, often offered free of charge.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="FINANCIAL KNOWLEDGE">
  <data key="d0">FINANCIAL_CONCEPT</data>
  <data key="d1">Financial Knowledge is an individual's understanding of financial concepts, products, and principles, essential for making informed financial decisions.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="FINANCIAL SKILLS">
  <data key="d0">FINANCIAL_CONCEPT</data>
  <data key="d1">Financial Skills are an individual's abilities to apply financial knowledge to manage money effectively and make informed decisions, contributing to financial empowerment.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="FINANCIAL CONFIDENCE">
  <data key="d0">FINANCIAL_CONCEPT</data>
  <data key="d1">Financial Confidence is an individual's self-assurance in their ability to handle financial matters and make sound financial decisions, often assessed in self-assessments.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="STRATEGIES FOR INCREASING INCOME AND BENEFITS">
  <data key="d0">FINANCIAL_CONCEPT</data>
  <data key="d1">Overall methods and plans aimed at boosting personal income and financial benefits, as reviewed in the document.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
<node id="TRADE SERVICES">
  <data key="d0">ACTION</data>
  <data key="d1">The strategy of exchanging services, such as house cleaning or babysitting for car repairs, with friends or relatives who have those skills.</data>
  <data key="d2">1</data>
</node>
