<edge source="ACTIVE DUTY SERVICEMEMBERS" target="CONSUMER LOANS">
  <data key="d3">14.0</data>
  <data key="d4">Consumer loans are offered to active duty servicemembers and their dependents. | Active duty servicemembers are recipients of various consumer loans, which are then subject to protections under the MLA.</data>
</edge>
<edge source="ACTIVE DUTY SERVICEMEMBERS" target="DEPENDENTS">
  <data key="d3">9.0</data>
  <data key="d4">The Military Lending Act extends its protections to both active duty servicemembers and their dependents.</data>
</edge>
<edge source="ACTIVE DUTY SERVICEMEMBERS" target="MILITARY LENDING ACT (MLA)">
  <data key="d3">9.0</data>
  <data key="d4">The Military Lending Act (MLA) provides special protections specifically for active duty servicemembers and their dependents regarding consumer loans.</data>
</edge>
<edge source="MILITARY LENDING ACT (MLA)" target="CONSUMER LOANS">
  <data key="d3">17.0</data>
  <data key="d4">Most consumer loans offered to active duty servicemembers must comply with the Military Lending Act. | The Military Lending Act (MLA) mandates compliance for most types of consumer loans offered to active duty servicemembers.</data>
</edge>
<edge source="MILITARY LENDING ACT (MLA)" target="DEPOSIT ADVANCE PRODUCTS">
  <data key="d3">16.0</data>
  <data key="d4">The Military Lending Act covers deposit advance products for active duty servicemembers. | Deposit advance products are explicitly listed as one of the credit products that must comply with the Military Lending Act for servicemembers.</data>
</edge>
<edge source="MILITARY LENDING ACT (MLA)" target="OVERDRAFT LINES OF CREDIT">
  <data key="d3">16.0</data>
  <data key="d4">The Military Lending Act covers overdraft lines of credit for active duty servicemembers. | Overdraft lines of credit are explicitly listed as one of the credit products that must comply with the Military Lending Act for servicemembers.</data>
</edge>
<edge source="MILITARY LENDING ACT (MLA)" target="INSTALLMENT LOANS">
  <data key="d3">16.0</data>
  <data key="d4">The Military Lending Act covers installment loans for active duty servicemembers (with exceptions). | Installment loans are explicitly listed as one of the credit products that must comply with the Military Lending Act for servicemembers, with some exceptions.</data>
</edge>
<edge source="MILITARY LENDING ACT (MLA)" target="SPECIAL PROTECTION">
  <data key="d3">9.0</data>
  <data key="d4">The Military Lending Act provides special protection for active duty servicemembers and their dependents regarding certain types of loans.</data>
</edge>
<edge source="MILITARY LENDING ACT (MLA)" target="SECURE LOANS">
  <data key="d3">6.0</data>
  <data key="d4">The Military Lending Act (MLA) specifically states that it does not cover certain secure loans, particularly those secured by property being purchased.</data>
</edge>
<edge source="MILITARY LENDING ACT (MLA)" target="RESIDENTIAL MORTGAGES">
  <data key="d3">6.0</data>
  <data key="d4">Residential mortgages are explicitly listed as a type of loan not covered by the Military Lending Act (MLA).</data>
</edge>
<edge source="MILITARY LENDING ACT (MLA)" target="MORTGAGE REFINANCES">
  <data key="d3">6.0</data>
  <data key="d4">Mortgage refinances are explicitly listed as a type of loan not covered by the Military Lending Act (MLA).</data>
</edge>
<edge source="MILITARY LENDING ACT (MLA)" target="HOME EQUITY LOANS">
  <data key="d3">6.0</data>
